A mala fide possessor had no actio furti, though the property was at his risk‚ Dig. 47. 2. 14. 4. The interest of the bona fide possessor, in virtue of which he could sue, was his right to the fruits and the interruption of usucapio, not his liability to the real dominus, which accrued only after the latter had joined issue with him in an action to establish his ownership, Dig. 5. 3. 25. 7.
